The paper deals with the problem of geospatial information extraction and representation using diverse sources of information, including text data. This involves the use of spatial reasoning and probabilistic modeling to quantify qualitative spatial relations. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (LG) techniques, which make cs.IR and cs.LG likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with spatial information (SI), which makes cs.SI a possible sub-category.
